A comparative study with rituximab (100 mg weekly for 4 weeks and 375mg/m2 for once) shows low dose rituximab may be a useful alternative therapy in patients with ITP.

The aim of this study is to compare the efficacy and tolerability of two different regimens of low doses rituximab for the treatment of adult patients with ITP.

